        sort_time: "2026-05-06 19:00:00",
        end_time_formatted: "2026-05-06 21:00:00",
        detail: "You Can Call Me Paul | May 9, 2026 7:00 PM | $31+ Event Details and Tickets\nBenjamin Falcon formed a love of the Simon & Garfunkel songbook while growing up outside of DC, in Alexandria, VA, through his parents fondness and nostalgia for Simon’s early work, as well as Falcon’s frequent exposure to the music in radio and media. In college, Falcon began to explore the larger catalogue of both Simon’s early and solo material.\n \“You can call me Paul\” has since sold out venues and attracted the collaboration of nationally touring musicians of note, including Jason Hann (The String Cheese Incident), Justin Ray (Michael Bublé), Justin Stanton (Snarky Puppy). This twelve-member band was assembled to authentically recreate the experience of seeing Simon’s solo work through the eras, in a live setting, with all the power and emotion that drew you to start.",
