        name: `Jason Bonham\'s Led Zeppelin Evening`,
        sort_time: "2026-06-03 19:30:00",
        end_time_formatted: "2026-06-03 23:59",
        detail: "Few drummers carry a legacy like Jason Bonham. At home behind the kit since childhood, he’s anchored the rhythm for some of rock’s most legendary artists — all while honoring the enduring spirit of his father, John Bonham of Led Zeppelin.\nFrom touring and recording with icons like Jimmy Page, John Paul Jones, and Robert Plant to powering Led Zeppelin’s historic 2007 reunion at London’s The O2 Arena — a show that set a Guinness World Record for highest ticket demand — Bonham has solidified his place in rock history. He’s also performed with Foreigner, Joe Bonamassa, Paul Rodgers, Sammy Hagar, and more.\nA little bit of \'The Wanton Song\' live with JBLZE from close up on drums.\n\nWith Jason Bonham’s Led Zeppelin Evening (JBLZE), he brings the thunder back to the stage in a powerful tribute packed with masterful musicianship, stunning visuals, and the timeless songs that defined a generation.\nJason Bonham isn’t just playing the drums — he’s carrying on a rock legacy.",
